The paper focuses on analyzing patterns of collaboration in co-authorship networks using a combination of qualitative and quantitative methods. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) as well as digital libraries (cs.DL) and social impact (cs.SI). However, given the emphasis on social organization and network analysis, cs.SOC and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
